⊕meta⊕
name = "archive-sky-workflow"
description = "Archive a .sky workflow into _archive/ with its trigger neutralized so it leaves the active path; reversible via restore mode. Manual gate before any move. Pure bash, no LLM."
trigger.manual = true
output_style = "terse"
ui = "ui/workflow"
⊕⊕

※find※
Resolve source/dest paths from $SKY_MODE (archive|restore); fail if source missing or dest exists.
※※

§find§
bash_file = "./scripts/find.sh"
ui = "ui/find"
§§

※gate※
Manual approval gate. Depends on find (all_success); 1h timeout. Shows source/dest paths and archive/restore implications before user approves the move.
※※

§gate§
depends_on = ["find"]
trigger_rule = "all_success"
wait.channel = "manual"
wait.prompt = "Confirm move. Archiving NEUTRALIZES the trigger so the file cannot auto-fire even if the loader scans _archive/. Restore returns it as a manual-only workflow (re-add a trigger to reactivate). Review the source and dest paths printed by the find step, then approve."
wait.timeout = "1h"
ui = "ui/gate"
§§

※move※
Move workflow to _archive/ (archive mode) or restore from it; strips trigger lines during archive to neutralize. Depends on gate (all_success).
※※

§move§
depends_on = ["gate"]
trigger_rule = "all_success"
bash_file = "./scripts/move.sh"
ui = "ui/move"
§§

※verify※
Lint the moved workflow file at its new location to confirm no syntax errors from the move. Depends on move (all_success).
※※

§verify§
depends_on = ["move"]
trigger_rule = "all_success"
bash_file = "./scripts/verify.sh"
ui = "ui/verify"
§§

※※
archive-sky-workflow
====================

Move a .sky workflow into an _archive/ subdir with its trigger neutralized so it
leaves the active load path, behind a manual gate. Reversible via restore mode.

Pure bash, no LLM: moving a file does not change its content, so the moved file
stays lint-clean and a bash `skyway lint` verify suffices. No token cost.

What archiving does to the trigger
----------------------------------
Archiving STRIPS every `^trigger.` line from the file (grep -v) before the move.
This NEUTRALIZES the trigger, so even if the loader ever scans _archive/, the
file cannot auto-fire. Restore moves the file back but leaves the trigger
neutralized: it returns as a manual-only workflow. Re-add a trigger line to
reactivate it.

DAG
---
  find ──> gate (manual) ──> move ──> verify

  find    resolve source/dest from mode; fail if source missing or dest exists
  gate    manual confirm (shows both paths via find output); 1h timeout
  move    archive: mkdir _archive, strip trigger lines, git mv (|| mv)
          restore: git mv (|| mv) back, trigger stays neutralized
  verify  skyway lint the moved file at its new path; nonzero exit on failure

Run
---
  archive (default):
    skyway run archive-sky-workflow --var dir=.sky/workflows --var name=old-flow
  restore:
    skyway run archive-sky-workflow --var dir=.sky/workflows --var name=old-flow --var mode=restore

Vars
----
  dir   directory holding the workflow (e.g. .sky/workflows)        -> $SKY_DIR
  name  workflow filename without .sky (e.g. old-flow)              -> $SKY_NAME
  mode  archive | restore; default archive when unset              -> $SKY_MODE
※※
